<dl id="n06155a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155a">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155a"> 155(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> all good things <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06155a"> <li>FW prototext </li><li><ms href="#n06155a">MS BL 47471b-10v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:151 <a name="c20d" href="../../FF/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06155a">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from the Twelfth Article of the Creed]</font> &ldquo;AMEN.&rdquo;&mdash;This is the Hebrew word, meaning true, certain, faithful. It is here used in token of undoubting assent. So I believe in <mark>these good things</mark> that pass man&apos;s understanding, which God has promised to them that love Him. <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 26</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
